The paper deals with recognizing human-human interactions in egocentric videos, which involves analyzing visual data and modeling relationships between individuals. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel deep learning framework for modeling these relationships, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on three different datasets, indicating that it may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
